analysis.title: Global Market Outlook
analysis.content: Market equilibrium hinges on macro-policy shifts. The GMS at 51 signifies an inflection point where the fiscal-monetary nexus faces renewed volatility following the judicial reversal of protectionist trade measures. While equity indices demonstrate residual momentum, the widening of high-yield credit spreads and a depressed sentiment index indicate latent fragility. The flat Copper/Gold vector mirrors stagnating real yields, suggesting that liquidity convexity remains capped. Contrarian risk lies in an abrupt repricing of inflation expectations if fiscal policy pivots further. [ACTION: WAIT FOR PULLBACK]
